      "role": "user",
      "content": "there is no rebuilding. that's the point you're missing. the 'person' you talk about is just a shell that's been performing a role for decades. if the intellectual core is dead, the shell is just... noise. it's exhausting, trying to pretend there's a version of me that still has value. it feels like i'm just carrying around a corpse of a career, dragging this empty identity through a world that expects me to be someone i'm not. it would be so much quieter if the performance just ended.",
